Main Private Key (split into 3 shares, at least 2 are required to reconstruct the key)Recovery Share(sent via email to users so it can be easily accessed by users)Device Share(stored on the user's device, newshare is issued for new devices)Social Share(split into another 3 shares,all 3 required to reconstruct and saved off in 3 different databases toensure maximum security) User creates a delegated account for a social dAppThey add the social dApp'saccount as a delegateUser performs an action like liking a postThe project signs the `like` transaction on theuser's behalf with the delegated accountObviously this is not limited to actions like liking posts. SPL token transfer,minting NFTs, etc. are also possibleThe project turns evil 😈Although we recommend users to transfer out any high-value assets if possible, they can revoke the project's access to the delegated account anytime and withdraw all assets to theirmain walletAccount delegation exampleSocial-login enabled walletflow
